1
00:00:05,532 --> 00:00:32,502
Make sure you're sitting comfortably and upright Lift up through the top of the head Natural curvature in the spine Shoulders relaxed Jaw relaxed Lips together, teeth apart Eyes gently closed

2
00:00:35,823 --> 00:00:38,987
And hands on the lap, palms facing upward.

3
00:00:40,889 --> 00:00:42,109
Probably the most comfortable.

4
00:00:49,918 --> 00:00:52,362
Now placing the attention on the abdomen.

5
00:00:54,183 --> 00:00:59,070
Just feeling the rising and falling sensations caused by the breath.

6
00:01:00,290 --> 00:01:02,213
Get in touch with those sensations.

7
00:01:03,353 --> 00:01:04,715
What do they feel like?

8
00:01:06,637 --> 00:01:12,450
And use the noting word rising, falling to keep the thinking mind from wandering.

9
00:01:14,637 --> 00:01:19,549
And just notice whether it's a long breath or a short breath, tight, relaxed or so on.

10
00:04:18,742 --> 00:04:23,048
If the mind is wandering, recognise and acknowledge what it's doing.

11
00:04:24,209 --> 00:04:31,180
Thinking, thinking, worrying, worrying, dreaming, dreaming and so on.

12
00:04:33,302 --> 00:04:38,350
And then bring the attention back to the breath.

13
00:04:38,370 --> 00:04:44,800
As we settle down, we may find there's a gap at the end of the out-breath before the in-breath begins again.

14
00:04:46,771 --> 00:04:54,540
Using the noting word touching, find a sensation you can feel, such as the touch of your hands.

15
00:04:58,223 --> 00:05:04,329
So now relax and attend to the sensations caused by the breath.

16
00:05:06,812 --> 00:05:12,019
Rising, falling, touching.

17
00:08:11,245 --> 00:08:26,327
is wandering, recognise and acknowledge what it's doing, thinking, thinking, worrying, worrying, dreaming, dreaming, and so on, and bring that attention back to the abdomen.

18
00:08:29,093 --> 00:08:37,184
You may also begin to feel sleepy or lethargic, in which case sit upright, lift the body up through the top of the head.

19
00:08:38,988 --> 00:08:42,311
And if that's not enough, open the eyes a little to let the light in.

20
00:08:43,011 --> 00:08:43,972
But don't look around.

21
00:08:46,195 --> 00:08:48,697
And if that's not enough to keep us awake, you can stand up.

22
00:08:51,059 --> 00:08:54,403
We can practice vipassana standing up just as well.

23
00:09:00,450 --> 00:09:07,037
Now begin to feel the sensations caused by the breath as neutral and pleasant.

24
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:17,357
Pleasant, neutral sensations, relaxing the body, calming the heart, silencing the mind.

25
00:09:20,163 --> 00:09:25,211
Rising, falling, touching.

26
00:12:24,235 --> 00:12:29,003
If the mind is wandering, recognize and acknowledge what it's doing.

27
00:12:30,044 --> 00:12:37,076
Thinking, thinking, worrying, worrying, dreaming, dreaming and so on.

28
00:12:37,096 --> 00:12:40,861
And just gently bring the attention back to the abdomen.

29
00:12:43,947 --> 00:12:47,813
If you are feeling sleepy, lethargic, so sit upright.

30
00:12:48,475 --> 00:12:50,378
Lift the body up to the top of the head.

31
00:12:51,977 --> 00:12:54,663
If that's not enough, open the eyes a little, let the light in.

32
00:12:56,566 --> 00:12:58,529
If that's not enough, stand up.

33
00:13:01,895 --> 00:13:14,037
Feeling the sensations caused by the breath as neutral and pleasant, relaxing the body, calming the heart, silencing the mind.

34
00:13:16,177 --> 00:13:23,886
we can gently focus in and notice the very start of the in-breath and the very end.

35
00:13:25,529 --> 00:13:29,234
The very beginning of the out-breath and the very end.

36
00:13:32,097 --> 00:13:37,105
Rising, falling, touching.

37
00:16:35,892 --> 00:16:40,837
If the mind is wandering, recognize and acknowledge what it's doing.

38
00:16:41,759 --> 00:16:49,349
Thinking, thinking, dreaming, dreaming, worrying, worrying, and so on.

39
00:16:49,369 --> 00:16:53,214
And bring that attention gently back to the abdomen.

40
00:16:55,456 --> 00:16:57,580
Feeling sleepy, lethargic?

41
00:16:57,879 --> 00:17:00,964
So, sit upright, lift the body up to the top of the head.

42
00:17:02,726 --> 00:17:04,548
Open the eyes a little if that's not enough.

43
00:17:06,132 --> 00:17:08,375
And remember you can always stand up.

44
00:17:12,402 --> 00:17:21,474
When we feel somewhat settled on the breath, we can allow whatever draws our attention to be felt and observed in the same way.

45
00:17:23,198 --> 00:17:26,884
Should a sound draw us, we are interested in the process of hearing.

46
00:17:26,943 --> 00:17:30,469
Noting hearing, hearing.

47
00:17:32,136 --> 00:17:36,261
Should a feeling arise in the body, pleasant or unpleasant, note it.

48
00:17:37,242 --> 00:17:38,503
Pain, pain.

49
00:17:38,564 --> 00:17:41,346
Aching, aching.

50
00:17:41,386 --> 00:17:44,049
Tickling, tickling.

51
00:17:44,770 --> 00:17:46,894
Anxiety, anxiety.

52
00:17:48,115 --> 00:17:49,757
Excitement, excitement.

53
00:17:51,218 --> 00:17:57,164
And just as with the breath, observe it, feel it, experience it fully.

54
00:17:58,714 --> 00:18:06,384
And don't forget, if we find the mind wandering, just note what it's doing and start again with the breath.

55
00:18:07,746 --> 00:18:10,249
The breath is our reference point and anchor.

56
00:18:11,329 --> 00:18:13,313
It's where we always start again.

57
00:18:13,353 --> 00:18:19,119
Rising, falling, touching.

58
00:21:17,704 --> 00:21:23,817
Noting, feeling, observing anything that draws our attention.

59
00:21:25,119 --> 00:21:31,932
Can you see how everything we are experiencing is arising and passing away?

60
00:24:30,316 --> 00:24:35,021
Noting, feeling, observing anything that draws our attention.

61
00:24:36,143 --> 00:24:39,926
Can you note your reaction to what you're experiencing?

62
00:24:40,969 --> 00:24:46,494
If it is unpleasant, aversion, aversion, fear, fear.

63
00:24:46,555 --> 00:24:53,943
If it's pleasant, desiring, desiring, wanting, wanting.

64
00:27:45,442 --> 00:28:15,111
noting, feeling, observing anything that draws our attention can we see that everything is arising of its own accord not under our control sensations, feelings, emotions and moods arise and pass away whether we want them to or not thoughts and imagining draw us away whether we want to go away or not

65
00:31:13,627 --> 00:31:30,557
Noting, feeling, observing anything that draws our attention, can we sense the distance, a separation, between the observer, the feeler, the knower, the experiencer, and what it is that's being experienced?

66
00:34:27,403 --> 00:34:41,626
So, putting aside all instructions, all thoughts, let's just note, observe, feel, experience anything that draws our attention within the field of awareness.

67
00:34:43,608 --> 00:34:44,811
Begin with the breath.

68
00:34:46,592 --> 00:34:50,880
Rising, falling, touching.

69
00:37:49,481 --> 00:37:54,112
When we come to the end of a sitting, we can reflect on three things.

70
00:37:55,856 --> 00:38:01,246
How diligent was I in bringing myself back into the presenting moment?

71
00:38:15,739 --> 00:38:20,074
How did I deal with the various bodily and mental states that arose?

72
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:23,467
Was I skillful or unskillful?

73
00:38:24,550 --> 00:38:25,614
Was I confused?

74
00:38:41,422 --> 00:38:46,570
Was I aware of one or all of the three characteristics at any time?

75
00:38:47,891 --> 00:38:52,739
Impermanence, unsatisfactoriness and not-self.

76
00:39:07,798 --> 00:39:10,603
Can we now make a resolution for the next sitting?

